Description: Papyrus; Hieroglyphic text, c. 101 fragments. This is a distinct text from the "Geographical papyrus"; the bottom of a text in columns, a festival-list. Hieratic and hieroglyphic notes below border lines. Now numbered 10673C.
Curator's comments: Not published in Griffith and Petrie, Two Hieroglyphic Papyri from Tanis (London, 1889). To be published by Jasnow.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380869) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380869)
Condition: Papyrus Survey: Condition Details: Papyrus: carbonised, brittle, salt precipitate, displaced fragments Black ink Adhered: gelatin (spots, cracked) Transferred to horizontal storage 30 DEC 94 Mount Details: Sandwich: glass (cracked) Binding: leather Object Priority: B Mount Priority: C Overall Condition: E Curatorial condition comment: poor
